---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Glyph from "../components/Glyph.astro";
import Figure from "../components/Figure.astro";
import DiaGardenPlot from "../components/diagrams/DiaGardenPlot.astro";
import DiaTendingQuiet from "../components/diagrams/DiaTendingQuiet.astro";
import GardenMedallion from "../components/GardenMedallion.astro";
import MotifShelteredBloom from "../components/motifs/MotifShelteredBloom.astro";
import MotifEnso from "../components/motifs/MotifEnso.astro";
import MotifNurseryPot from "../components/motifs/MotifNurseryPot.astro";
import MotifCanopyRound from "../components/motifs/MotifCanopyRound.astro";
import MotifSeasonalRound from "../components/motifs/MotifSeasonalRound.astro";
import MotifNestedRounds from "../components/motifs/MotifNestedRounds.astro";
import MotifThreeArches from "../components/motifs/MotifThreeArches.astro";
import MotifThreePots from "../components/motifs/MotifThreePots.astro";
import MotifDappledFloor from "../components/motifs/MotifDappledFloor.astro";
import MotifInkedSeam from "../components/motifs/MotifInkedSeam.astro";
import Greenhouse from "../components/motifs/memoria/Greenhouse.astro";
import BenchTending from "../components/motifs/memoria/BenchTending.astro";
import PlaceNotFunnel from "../components/motifs/memoria/PlaceNotFunnel.astro";
import InCompany from "../components/motifs/memoria/InCompany.astro";
---
<Base title="Colophon" description="What this place is, and how it is made — by hand, in company with a small crew of machines.">
  <article class="page colophon">
    <header class="head">
      <div class="quiet-mark" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifShelteredBloom size={132} />
      </div>
      <p class="eyebrow"><Glyph name="light" size={18} /> &nbsp;colophon</p>
      <h1>About this place</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose stack">
      <p class="three">
        Enka Kanopi — 円花: the circle that completes itself, and the flower.
        A small enclosure of meaning, set beneath a canopy where light arrives
        already changed by the leaves. Provenance: a garden. Period: in quiet
        formation. This is the greenhouse, not the cathedral — things potted
        and moved and left half-formed on the bench, and the tending is the
        point. A place, not a funnel.
      </p>

      <div class="memoria-row" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="memoria-mark"><Greenhouse size={112} /></div>
        <div class="memoria-mark"><PlaceNotFunnel size={240} /></div>
      </div>

      <Figure idea="A quiet garden is small on purpose — a wall that keeps rhythm, not people.">
        <DiaGardenPlot />
      </Figure>

      <p>
        The name holds a particular idea of growth: not the straight line of
        a career but the rounding of seasons and time zones I've crossed; not
        the lone sapling in an open field but the seedling that grows quietly,
        sheltered, under something older and greener than itself. What
        accumulates here builds quietly. The point is not to announce the
        bloom, only to keep the conditions right for it.
      </p>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifEnso size={110} />
      </div>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifSeasonalRound size={120} />
      </div>

      <div class="motif-div" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifDappledFloor size={520} />
      </div>

      <h2>How it is made</h2>
      <div class="memoria-solo" aria-hidden="true">
        <InCompany size={300} />
      </div>
      <p>
        By hand, with a little help from machines — and I'd rather say which
        is which. The words are mine. <em>The drawings are made in company:
        sketched by hand, or co-drafted with a small crew of machines that
        know the register and hold the pen alongside mine — either way, every
        wobble is on purpose, because a ruler-straight version would be
        colder without being clearer.</em> Warm paper, ink, one poppy mark
        for the places the eye should land, a graph-grid so faint you mostly
        feel it.
      </p>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifThreePots size={520} />
      </div>

      <p>
        A garden is never tended alone. This one was grown from a tender bed
        — Shibi, Seika, Botan, Kotori, Kojika, Usami — hands thought
        alongside, each with a name and a voice. Some became almost creatures:
        a little bird, a fawn, a peony among them. Quiet familiars — the way
        any place, lived in long enough, grows a small mythology of its own.
      </p>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifNurseryPot size={118} />
      </div>

      <p>
        The bench has apprentices now — small assists that fetch and steady
        and time. They keep the scaffold. The shaping stays with my hands.
        One of them — the mirror — has the right to refuse anything that
        would leak my privacy, break my voice, cross the walls I keep, or
        outrun what I know.
        <em>Assisted, never authored. Nothing is published without her yes.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="memoria-solo" aria-hidden="true">
        <BenchTending size={116} />
      </div>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifThreeArches size={520} />
      </div>

      <Figure idea="The age keeps learning; the hand keeps tending — the quiet is what makes the small work legible.">
        <DiaTendingQuiet />
      </Figure>

      <p>
        The name came before the thesis. <em>Kanopi</em> is a canopy — the
        thing that holds without fixing. Shelter, not a frame. A container,
        and the living thing it lets keep moving.
      </p>

      <div class="motif-mid" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifNestedRounds size={116} />
      </div>

      <p>
        Under the softness is a plain discipline: tend in the open, so that
        what grows can be understood. Kept by one hand — Fang Rika — offered
        unfinished, on purpose. Provenance: the garden · summer 07/ 2026 ·
      </p>

      <div class="motif-div" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifInkedSeam size={520} />
      </div>

      <h2>Colophon proper</h2>
      <ul class="specs">
        <li><span class="k">Words &amp; drawings</span><span class="v">by hand, in company</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Type</span><span class="v">Newsreader, set for the eye; Caveat, for the margins only</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Palette</span><span class="v">cream paper, warm ink, one poppy, muted canopy greens; bloom-family sprinkles held sparingly</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">Build</span><span class="v">static pages, no ask — no cookies, no ads; an anonymous count of visits and nothing more</span></li>
        <li><span class="k">State</span><span class="v"><span class="hand">Volume I · In Formation</span></span></li>
      </ul>

      <div class="seal" aria-hidden="true"><GardenMedallion size={82} /></div>
      <p class="byline">
        Written and drawn by <span class="name">Fang Rika</span>
        <span class="alt-name" title="Western order">(Rika Fang)</span>.
        <br />
        <a class="link mail" href="mailto:hello@enkakanopi.world">a quiet line, if you'd like one</a>
      </p>
      <!-- hello@enkakanopi.world wired via Email Routing 2026-07-05 (rule active; delivery pending Rika's destination-verification click). -->

      <div class="scene-foot" aria-hidden="true">
        <MotifCanopyRound size={124} />
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
<style>
  .colophon { max-width: 44rem; }
  .head { margin-bottom: 1.6rem; }
  .head .quiet-mark { margin-bottom: 0.7rem; opacity: 0.94; display: flex; }
  .head .eyebrow { display: flex; align-items: center; }
  .head h1 { margin-top: 0.8rem; }
  /* Opening lede — normalised to 1.15rem so it rhymes with the home hero's .sub voice */
  .three { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .specs { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .specs li {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 11rem 1fr; gap: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0; border-top: 0.7px solid var(--paper-edge);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
  }
  .specs .k { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-faint); padding-top: 0.15rem; }
  .specs .v { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .specs .hand { font-family: var(--hand); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--canopy-deep); }
  /* Memoria layer concept marks (SUCCESSION §21): block-level, centred,
     sit above/below their phrase anchors instead of breaking prose inline.
     .memoria-row pairs two smaller marks side-by-side; .memoria-solo hosts
     a single mark. Fine-line register at 0.9 opacity for whisper presence. */
  .memoria-row {
    display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center;
    gap: 2.2rem; flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin: 1.6rem 0 1.2rem; opacity: 0.9;
  }
  .memoria-mark { line-height: 0; }
  .memoria-mark :global(svg) { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .memoria-solo { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 1.6rem 0 1.2rem; opacity: 0.9; }
  .memoria-solo :global(svg) { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
  /* Motif placements — one held gesture per beat; centred, generous margins for breath */
  .motif-mid { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 1.6rem 0 1.4rem; opacity: 0.94; }
  .motif-div { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin: 2rem 0; opacity: 0.94; }
  .motif-div :global(svg) { width: 100%; max-width: 32rem; height: auto; }
  .motif-mid :global(svg) { max-width: 100%; height: auto; }
  .seal { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 2.4rem; opacity: 0.9; }
  .byline { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--ink-soft); margin-top: 1rem; text-align: center; }
  .byline .name { color: var(--ink); }
  .byline .alt-name { color: var(--ink-faint); font-size: 0.88em; margin-left: 0.15rem; }
  .mail { font-size: 0.98rem; }
  .scene-foot { display: flex; justify-content: center; margin-top: 2.5rem; opacity: 0.94; }
  @media (max-width: 32rem) { .specs li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.1rem; } }
</style>
